{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":2041,"name":"","username":"vivienneanthony","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/vivienneanthony/{size}/942_2.png","created_at":"2014-08-11T13:21:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI find this link interesting. Maybe something like it can be used for texturing terrain in Urho3D in a generated imaged that can be also saved if need be.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://dice.se/wp-content/uploads/Chapter5-Andersson-Terrain_Rendering_in_Frostbite.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003edice.se/wp-content/uploads/Chapt … stbite.pdf\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m just seeing if someone can take a look. I don’t know Urho3D good enougth to build a shader to class function to implement something like this.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdeas…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eVivienne\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:00:00.710Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":11,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":56.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":383,"topic_slug":"frostbite-terrain-texturing","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://dice.se/wp-content/uploads/Chapter5-Andersson-Terrain_Rendering_in_Frostbite.pdf","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":88,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":2102,"name":"","username":"vivienneanthony","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/vivienneanthony/{size}/942_2.png","created_at":"2014-08-15T14:16:05.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=“Sinoid”]As I understand it the FrostBite technique is more about tools than anything else. From what I could gather (I’ve read it multiple times - over the past few years) it appears to use “mini-shaders” that they composite together for the chunks/patches of terrain (they do similar in clumping their masks as being more like a “Texture Region” of a texture-atlas).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat sort of thing (the shader, not the chunking) is probably a pretty decent place to get dirty with learning shaders in just about any environment. Terrain is ‘regular’ so there’s a fair bit less to have to deal with.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.horde3d.org/wiki/index.php5?title=Shading_Technique_-_Dot_Product_Detail_Texturing\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehorde3d.org/wiki/index.php5? … _Texturing\u003c/a\u003e - here’s an example of a shader doing that in Horde (wrote that wiki article a long long time ago)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBecause terrain is regular, you could also take it a bit further and do some Von Neuman (to find XY slopes) sampling to perturb the normal for lighting. With a decent colormap even that old technique can still get some pretty good results.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI almost got procedural working fully in Urho3D with a lot of help. The link is at \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/procedural-generated-worlds/335/1\"\u003eProcedural Generated Worlds\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe quicker that \u003ca href=\"http://libnoise.sourceforge.net/tutorials/tutorial5.html\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003elibnoise.sourceforge.net/tutoria … rial5.html\u003c/a\u003e can be implemented or some type.  Maybe texturing would be the nice project.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:00:05.368Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":1.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":383,"topic_slug":"frostbite-terrain-texturing","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://libnoise.sourceforge.net/tutorials/tutorial5.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"libnoise: Tutorial 5: Creating more complex terrain","clicks":0},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/procedural-generated-worlds/335","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Procedural Generated Worlds","clicks":0},{"url":"http://www.horde3d.org/wiki/index.php5?title=Shading_Technique_-_Dot_Product_Detail_Texturing","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Shading Technique - Dot Product Detail Texturing - Horde3D Wiki","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":88,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":8972,"name":"","username":"namic","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/779978/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-12-12T01:57:48.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt seems that they use a very similar workflow that the one used here: \u003ca href=\"http://unigine.com/en/articles/procedural-content-generation2\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eunigine.com/en/articles/procedur … eneration2\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:08:35.455Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":1.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":383,"topic_slug":"frostbite-te